This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it presents a new predictive model based on a two-level neural attention mechanism. It also involves the use of recurrent neural networks (RNN) and traditional models such as logistic regression, which are commonly used in machine learning. 

It could also belong to cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) as it involves the application of machine learning to Electronic Health Records (EHR) data, which is a form of computational science. 

Additionally, it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the development of a new predictive model that uses neural attention mechanisms, which is a subfield of AI. 

It could also belong to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as it involves the use of EHR data in healthcare, which is a field that involves the interaction between humans and computers. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves the use of EHR data to predict future outcomes, which is a form of information retrieval.
